Alternatively, we can model the palindrome as a string of 15 letters where the first 8 letters determine the rest. Therefore, we can think of the problem as counting the number of strings of length 8 (determining the first 8 letters) such that when mirrored, the resulting 15-letter palindrome contains "ARML" as a substring.
